From 90a57ff47f6b34ddcbf045d8ee6d984b593ca4f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 18:01:28 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 12/13] eink: add screensaver dream + lock/unlock e-ink refresh
 hooks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds an EinkDreamService (SystemUI-hosted DreamService) that renders a
white background with a crescent-moon + Zzz glyph, with a user-controlled
opacity (Settings.System.eink_screensaver_alpha, default 100). The dream
forces a full e-ink panel refresh on entry and exit so the moon frame
draws cleanly and is removed cleanly on wake.

The dream is registered as the device-default screensaver AND the doze
component (latter via the EInkFrameworkOverlay RRO in vendor/extra), so
it runs during the AWAKE-to-ASLEEP transition without being torn down by
PowerManagerService.handleSandman — non-doze dreams are not permitted in
ASLEEP wakefulness, only doze dreams are. The dream itself never calls
startDozing(); on e-ink the panel persists the last frame natively, so
no low-power AOD mode is needed.

EinkCenterController.start() writes Settings.Secure.SCREENSAVER_COMPONENTS
to our component on first boot if unset (the framework-res RRO override
of config_dreamsDefaultComponent only seeds default-component on initial
SettingsProvider DB creation; this fixup makes the active screensaver
deterministic on devices whose Settings DB pre-existed our build).

EinkCenterController also subscribes to ACTION_USER_PRESENT and triggers
IEinkManager.forceFullRefresh() on every keyguard dismiss, so the
lockscreen-to-app transition does not carry ghosting from the keyguard
frame.

Files: packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/eink/screensaver/EinkDreamService.java  (new)
  packages/SystemUI/res/layout/eink_dream.xml  (new)
  packages/SystemUI/res/xml/eink_dream_metadata.xml  (new)
  packages/SystemUI/res/drawable-nodpi/ic_eink_moon_zzz.png  (new)
  packages/SystemUI/AndroidManifest.xml  (dream service entry)
  packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/eink/EinkCenterController.java
    (USER_PRESENT receiver + boot-time SCREENSAVER_COMPONENTS write)
Change-Id: I95b2b0ce8fd132fc176901a3b84d4bf59cb3e580
